        public TokenEntity createToken​(ParticipantEntity participantEntity,
                               PollEntity pollEntity,
                               java.lang.Boolean trackingEnabled)
        Creates a new Token. If tracking is enabled the reference to the participant Entity will also be stored in the token. Currently not used.
        Parameters:
        participantEntity - participant this token belongs to (only stored if tracking Enabled is true)
        pollEntity - the poll this token belongs to
        trackingEnabled - If true, reference to participant is stored permanently
        Returns:
        created toked

      • createToken

        public TokenEntity createToken​(ParticipantEntity participantEntity,
                               java.lang.String token,
                               java.lang.Boolean trackingEnabled)
        Creates a new Token based on parameters. If tracking is enabled the reference to the participant Entity will also be stored in the token.
        Parameters:
        participantEntity - the Participant entity this token should belong to (only stored if tracking Enabled is true) Also used to get poll reference
        token - string representing a unique token value
        trackingEnabled - If true, reference to participant is stored permanently as well
        Returns:
        token object
